instruction:
Every C++ program starts at `main()`. `cout` (console out) prints output. `endl` ends the line.

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    cout << "Hello!" << endl;
    return 0;
}
```

`<<` is the stream insertion operator — it pushes data into `cout`. Hit **Run**.

starter:
